The Company develops, manufactures and sells a wide range of proprietary stone surface finish products, designed for use in interior and exterior applications to vertical and horizontal surfaces. The products are well suited for both commercial and residential buildings, often in specialized applications not possible with traditional stone and cement-based building surface products. The Company’s technologically advanced building surface products are applied during the construction and/or renovation process and are comprised of water-based, cross-link polymers combined with natural stone and recycled glass aggregate, resulting in a highly attractive finish. Designed as specialized surface finishes, not as base (substrate) materials, the Fluid Stone line of products are cost-competitive alternatives to the materials for which it is designed as a substitute: plaster, stucco, vinyl and wood siding, masonry veneer, linoleum, tile, marble and granite.

Organization Name: Smecoils - Water coils and Chilled water coils
Description: Water Coils can be used for a single purpose such as heating or cooling
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Optimize HVAC chilled water coils with coil coatings HVAC chilled water coils are the backbone of the many commercial and industrial HVAC operations, keeping temperature levels within optimal ranges and allowing daily business functions to continue unimpeded. For industries that need constant cooling and temperature regulation, like refineries, commercial food refrigeration and data centers, not only are HVAC chilled water coils necessary for safe and efficient business operations, but also for remaining compliant with the newest state and federal energy guidelines. Preventing improper water flow The temperature level of incoming air is far over its requisite outtake into the building. However, this function is merely capable if the water running through the coils is doing so at an appropriate speed and is making contact with the inside walls of the coils. and since chilled water coils are designed with more rows than their quandary counterparts, surface contact is of even greater importance because forced air contains a longer route to travel before entering a building. If water isn’t properly chilling the coils, the whole process is wasting energy and money. Using HVAC coil coatings HVAC units housed in harsh environments, like those with high levels of salt and pollutants, have a far taller task in creating optimal HVAC conditions. Copper and aluminum coils may be especially tormented by these elements and start to corrode over time if necessary preventative measures aren't taken. Some of the primary signs of poor coil performance are small pinhole leaks and craters along the coil walls. When water and air are allowed to leak of the coils, the complete cooling capability of the system is in danger of degradation, and ultimately, malfunction. Additionally, small dimples that form within the coils decrease the surface contact potential of the chilled water, making the unit work harder to cool down forced air. If these problems still worsen, chilled water coils can actually break, and must get replaced immediately.

Description: Clean Energy Innovations develops & markets a proprietary process capable of delivering an increase of at least 25% in the energy extracted.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Clean Energy Innovations develops and markets a proprietary process capable of delivering an increase of at least 25% in the energy extracted from a battery during one discharge cycle.  The CEI process promises to be a critical factor in the growth of rechargeable batteries which is expected to be a $50 billion market by 2015.  Despite large R & D investment in the industry, the rate of performance improvement is relatively slow.  Dramatic improvements in cost, performance, or weight of rechargeable batteries will add high value to the end products where they are used. The CEI reproducible laboratory test results of its patent pending process, IPS™ (Interfacial Process Stimulation), demonstrate its claims for significant performance improvements in both Nickel Metal Hydride and Lithium Ion batteries.  The process will work with any type of rechargeable battery. The IPS™ process can be readily integrated into existing control systems, by adding a simple low cost logic component into the battery power management modules.  This means there is a minimal amount of incremental development and incremental bill-of-material cost. This is a disruptive technology which brings immediate performance results that match the more costly industry developments underway in battery chemistries and controls.  Through the implementation of software-driven advances in the operating system of the battery, IPS™ achieves clear improvements, but is also compatible and synergistic with these R & D efforts.   Key is that CEI’s process has been shown to be far more cost effective - it achieves the same results with a lower investment by at least four orders of magnitude.  CEI seeks partnership arrangements with market leaders where IPS™ will be a major driver to advances within important industry sectors such as mobile devices, electric vehicles and storage for renewable energy installations.  CEI has a passion for solutions that support the major global objectives for environmental health and security, energy independence, and economic growth.  CEI believes that IPS™ will have a major impact on these important objectives.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Energy, Hardware, Manufacturing, Natural Resources, Sustainability

Description: Webepags is an online database platform that allows people to easily edit, add, and query for data.
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Webepags is an online database platform that allows people to easily edit, add, and query for data.  The data is stored in RDF format, so this makes it easier for other web applications to use the data stored in webepags.   The platform is geared toward both consumers and developers.  Consumers appreciate the search tools and the way that the data is displayed in a simple, easy to understand format.  There is also a search feature that allows a user to enter a block of text and for the retrieval of facts by words in the text.  There is also an ontology feature that makes sure that words meaning the same thing as another are also included.  For example, seeing as the term "Mozart" is used frequently to refer to "Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart," the ontology feature is able to recognize this in searches.
